在Vue.js中，你可以把一个数值保留一位小数并显示，有两种常见方法：

方法一：使用Vue过滤器来格式化数值

你可以在Vue组件中使用过滤器来格式化数值，以下是一个保留一位小数的例子:

```html
<template>
  <div>
    <p>{{ value | roundOneDecimalPlace}}</p>
  </div>
</template>

<script>
export default {
  data() {
    return {
      value: 10.56789
    }
  },
  filters: {
    roundOneDecimalPlace(value) {
      return value.toFixed(1);
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

在上述代码中，`roundOneDecimalPlace`过滤器接受一个数值，并使用`toFixed(1)`方法将其舍入到小数点后一位。在模板中，通过管道符(|)把value传递给过滤器来显示格式化后的数值。

方法二：在JavaScript中使用toFixed()方法格式化数值

你也可以在Vue.js组件中使用toFixed()方法来格式化数值，如下所示：

```html
<template>
  <div>
    <p>{{ value.toFixed(1)}}</p>
  </div>
</template>

<script>
export default {
  data() {
    return {
      value: 10.56789
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

在上述代码中，通过在`value`变量后面调用`.toFixed()`方法来格式化数值，传递小数点后要保留的位数。在模板中，Vue.js将渲染格式化后的值。

无论你选择哪种方法，注意，`toFixed()`方法将数值转换为一串带有指定小数点后位数的字符串。如果需要将其转换回数字，请使用`parseFloat()`或`Number()`函数进行转换。

The issue is caused by the `gsap.to` method. It seems like GSAP's `scrollTo` is having trouble directly applying the scrollTo on `window`. Instead, you can create a scroll animation on a container element (e.g., a div) and set its `scrollTop` value.

Here's an example on how you can achieve the scroll animation by wrapping the content in a container:

```html
<template>
  <div>
    <button ref="prevBtn" @click="scrollToPreviousSection">Previous</button>
    <button ref="nextBtn" @click="scrollToNextSection">Next</button>

    <div ref="container" class="container" style="height: 100vh; overflow-y: scroll;">
      <section ref="heroSection" class="hero">Hero</section>
      <section ref="aboutSection" class="about">About</section>
      <section ref="featuresSection" class="features">Features</section>
      <section ref="footerSection" class="footer">Footer</section>
    </div>
  </div>
</template>

<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue';
import { gsap } from 'gsap';
import { ScrollToPlugin } from 'gsap/ScrollToPlugin';
gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollToPlugin);

const prevBtn = ref(null);
const nextBtn = ref(null);
const container = ref(null);
const heroSection = ref(null);
const aboutSection = ref(null);
const featuresSection = ref(null);
const footerSection = ref(null);

const scrollToPreviousSection = () => {
  const currentSection = getCurrentSection();
  const previousSection = getPreviousSection(currentSection);
  scrollToSection(previousSection);
};

const scrollToNextSection = () => {
  const currentSection = getCurrentSection();
  const nextSection = getNextSection(currentSection);
  scrollToSection(nextSection);
};

const getCurrentSection = () => {
  const sections = [heroSection.value, aboutSection.value, featuresSection.value, footerSection.value];
  const currentSection = sections.find((section) => {
    const rect = section.getBoundingClientRect();
    const containerRect = container.value.getBoundingClientRect();
    return rect.top >= containerRect.top && rect.bottom <= containerRect.bottom;
  });
  return currentSection;
};

const getPreviousSection = (currentSection) => {
  const sections = [heroSection.value, aboutSection.value, featuresSection.value, footerSection.value];
  const currentIndex = sections.indexOf(currentSection);
  return sections[currentIndex - 1] || heroSection.value;
};

const getNextSection = (currentSection) => {
  const sections = [heroSection.value, aboutSection.value, featuresSection.value, footerSection.value];
  const currentIndex = sections.indexOf(currentSection);
  return sections[currentIndex + 1] || footerSection.value;
};

const scrollToSection = (section) => {
  gsap.to(container.value, {
    scrollTo: {
      y: section.offsetTop,
      autoKill: false,
    },
    duration: 1,
    ease: 'power2.inOut',
  });
};
</script>

<style scoped>
section {
  height: 100vh;
}
</style>
```

In this example, I wrapped the sections within a div with the `container` ref and applied the scrollTo to `container.value`. Also, make sure you import and register the `ScrollToPlugin` from GSAP.

