I apologize for the confusion. Let's fix the hover underline effect on your navigation bar. Replace the existing `nav ul li a::after` and `nav ul li a:hover::after` CSS styles with the following styles:

```css
nav ul li a {
  position: relative;
}

nav ul li a::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 2px;
  background-color: #000;
  transform: scaleX(0);
  transition: transform 0.3s;
}

nav ul li a:hover::after {
  transform: scaleX(1);
}
```

This will create a smooth underline effect when hovering over the navigation links, while keeping the navigation bar in the correct order and position.

