It seems you have a basic structure of your project set up. I will provide some recommendations for you to improve your code.

1. Separate PHP and HTML in your files: Instead of mixing PHP and HTML, you can separate the PHP parts into different files and include them in your HTML files, which makes your project more manageable.

For example, create a new file called `index_process.php` and move the PHP code from `index.php` to this new file.

index_process.php:

```php
<?php
include 'database.php';
session_start();

function process_login()
{
    global $conn;

    if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] == 'POST') {
        $username = $_POST['username'];
        $password = $_POST['password'];

        if (empty($username) || empty($password)) {
            return array('error' => 'All fields are required');
        } else {
            $stmt = $conn->prepare("SELECT * FROM users_data WHERE username = ? AND password=?");
            $stmt->bind_param("ss", $username , $password);
            $stmt->execute();
            $result = $stmt->get_result();
            if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
                $row = $result->fetch_assoc();
                if($row["id"] == 1){
                    header("Location: admin_page/admin_page.php");
                    exit();
                }
                else{
                    header("Location: user_page/user_page.php");
                    exit();
                }
            } else {
                return array('error' => 'Invalid username or password');
            }
        }
    }
}

$errors = process_login();
```

Now include this file in your `index.php` file just before the HTML opening tag:

index.php:
```php
<?php
include 'index_process.php';
?>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  ...
</html>
```

You can also refer to this guide on [How to Separate PHP and HTML Properly](https://www.codementor.io/@meghna83/how-to-separate-php-and-html-properly-m2772mo2c).

2. Use modern frontend tools and libraries: You are currently using plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript without using any frontend frameworks or libraries. You can use modern frontend tools and libraries like React, Angular, Vue, or even Bootstrap to make your project more modern, fast, and user-friendly.

3. Implement a proper session management: Currently, you're initiating sessions but not managing them properly. Make sure to store user data in session after successful login, and create a proper authentication system to identify users before they can access user-specific pages.

4. Use prepared statement for all database queries: In your `user_page.php` file, you have included `database.php` but not used prepared statements. Make sure to always use prepared statements for all database queries to avoid SQL injection vulnerabilities.

5. Implement a proper logout functionality by destroying the user session when the user clicks on the "Log Out" button.

6. Validate user input: Before processing any form input, ensure that the input data is valid and doesn't contain any special characters that might cause security issues or unexpected behavior.

In summary, you have a basic structure, but there's room for improvement in terms of code organization, frontend design, user experience, session management, and security. Focus on these aspects to enhance your project. Keep coding and good luck with your project!

